  "doc_id": "23835",
  "text": "Immune cells, especially liver macrophages (Kupffer cells), also play a pivotal role in hepatic fibrosis. In response to liver injury, massive Kupffer cells recruit to the liver, and produce inflammatory cytokines (such as TGF-β1), which perpetuate inflammation and mediate HSC activation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Our result indicated that IH could effectively inhibit inflammation and regulate Kupffer cell recruitment in the chronic damaged liver, which contributed to the alleviation of liver fibrosis caused by chronic CCl 4 and cholestasis exposure [CITATION_3] .",
